'2025-11-19 06:26:24.790','https://res.cloudinary.com/dajcb1ir2/raw/upload/v1763533584/NovelVerse/books/the-great-gatsby/hzx7pcrw09mcpvh6r48p.json',1,'the-great-gatsby'),('e826da2a-f61b-457d-90a8-cd929ae4e7f6','The Selfish Gene','Richard Dawkins','The Selfish Gene presents an influential gene-centered view of evolution, arguing that natural selection operates primarily on genes, which behave in ways to maximize their own replication. Dawkins explores how seemingly altruistic behaviors can arise from \'selfish\' genetic interests, and introduces the concept of the \'meme\'—a unit of cultural evolution analogous to the gene. The book challenges traditional organism- or group-centered views of evolution and explains complex social behaviors through genetic strategies.','1976-03-01 00:00:00.000','Science & Technology','https://imgs.search.brave.com/lrAqJ5OKf2h5mveQ8J7TZPAfG03gZfyyk-52KKfK_qE/rs:fit:500:0:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9ydWtt/aW5pbTIuZmxpeGNh/cnQuY29tL2ltYWdl/LzMxMi8zMTIveGlm/MHEvYm9vay9xL2Qv/ei90aGUtc2VsZmlz/aC1nZW5lLW9yaWdp/bmFsLWltYWhmNWhi/YjIzeWNxaHQuanBl/Zz9xPTcwJmNyb3A9/ZmFsc2U','2025-10-24 14:09:47.546',NULL,0,'English',385,'https://alraziuni.edu.ye/uploads/pdf/The-Selfish-Gene-R.-Dawkins-1976-WW-.pdf','2025-11-19 06:36:44.189','https://res.cloudinary.com/dajcb1ir2/raw/upload/v1763534203/NovelVerse/books/the-selfish-gene/s1knj1byjwioy8zpgjjj.json',1,'the-selfish-gene'),('eb8baeb1-1c98-4316-bf16-90a8a3a75e3c','Zero to One: Notes on Startups, or How to Build the Future','Peter Thiel with Blake Masters','Zero to One explores how to innovate and create unique value in the business world rather than copying others. Peter Thiel argues that the next generation of successful startups will not build on existing ideas, but will go from \'zero to one\' by developing singular innovations. Combining insights from his Stanford lectures and startup experiences, he offers guidance on building monopolies through creativity, vision, and long-term strategic thinking.','2014-09-16 00:00:00.000','Finance & Business','https://imgs.search.brave.com/ozF_lMHHxryHJZhmBogR-VhHwsUOAu-_u8BG0fnjHVQ/rs:fit:500:0:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9tZWRp/YS5saWNkbi5jb20v/ZG1zL2ltYWdlL0M0/RTEyQVFHLWoxU0VX/RVUzQXcvYXJ0aWNs/ZS1jb3Zlcl9pbWFn/ZS1zaHJpbmtfNzIw/XzEyODAvMC8xNTg4/MzQ2NjAwNTEwP2U9/MjE0NzQ4MzY0NyZ2/PWJldGEmdD13RV81/OUNhUjFWeW5NbjQ0/NjZTRGU2aXV3VDVy/MHRPSU9lTnNSQkFy/Z0pN','2025-10-24 13:44:38.529',NULL,1,'English',160,'https://morfene.com/021.pdf','2025-11-19 06:42:29.848','https://res.cloudinary.com/dajcb1ir2/raw/upload/v1763534549/NovelVerse/books/zero-to-one:-notes-on-startups%2C-or-how-to-build-the-future/q4idybzeq4k3n8ath4tl.json',1,'zero-to-one:-notes-on-startups,-or-how-to-build-the-future'),('f56f70f1-f988-4625-bb9f-b21ac8681e4d','Ikigai','Francesc Miralles','Ikigai explores the Japanese secret to a long, fulfilling, and happy life by uncovering how purpose, balance, and community influence well-being and longevity. It blends ancient wisdom with modern research to help readers find their own \'reason for being\'—the intersection of what they love, what they are good at, what the world needs, and what they can be paid for.','2016-09-27 00:00:00.000','Self-Help & Personal Development','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/15095588-L.jpg','2025-10-24 13:15:53.709',NULL,1,'English',131,'https://dn721607.ca.archive.org/0/items/ikigai-the-japanese-secret-to-a-long-and-happy-life-by-hector-garcia-and-francesc-miralles-2016-2003/Ikigai%20The%20Japanese%20Secret%20to%20a%20Long%20and%20Happy%20Life%20by%20Hector%20Garcia%20and%20%20Francesc%20Miralles%202016.pdf','2025-11-19 06:46:22.569','https://res.cloudinary.com/dajcb1ir2/raw/upload/v1763534782/NovelVerse/books/ikigai/mxsbnayq3vbyvxegjclt.json',1,'ikigai'),('fcf13bc1-1b72-4c21-bc30-9fe33c417aa2','Man’s Search for Meaning','Viktor E. Frankl','Man’s Search for Meaning chronicles Viktor Frankl’s harrowing experiences as a prisoner in Nazi concentration camps and outlines his psychotherapeutic theory of logotherapy. The book illustrates how finding meaning—through work, love, or embracing suffering—can enable individuals to survive unimaginable hardships. Frankl emphasizes that even in the worst conditions, humans retain the freedom to choose their attitude, which shapes their resilience and purpose in life. This profound work highlights the importance of meaning in personal well-being and existential fulfillment.','1946-01-01 00:00:00.000','Philosophy & Spirituality','https://imgs.search.brave.com/ZMkwahPpFnwcZDwRi9L1fuJnJIcHL-jQXv18CA6oGB8/rs:fit:500:0:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9pLmVi/YXlpbWcuY29tL2lt/YWdlcy9nL0lwSUFB/ZVN3RXlCb3hhZW4v/cy1sMjI1LmpwZw','2025-10-24 16:48:59.836',NULL,0,'English',69,'https://antilogicalism.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/mans-search-for-meaning.pdf','2025-11-19 06:48:46.525','https://res.cloudinary.com/dajcb1ir2/raw/upload/v1763534926/NovelVerse/books/man%E2%80%99s-search-for-meaning/zlatiwafsiaqvbwsbsam.json',1,'man’s-search-for-meaning');
